        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Require multipart package publishes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Require `multipart/form-data` for `POST /api/v1/packages`; JSON package publish bodies now fail before publish actions run.\n- Keep public package publish payloads metadata-only: caller-supplied `payload.files`, `payload.artifact`, multipart `artifact`, `files[]`, `tarball`, and other unsupported fields are rejected.\n- Preserve the released multipart API shapes the CLI uses: `payload` + repeated `files` uploads, or `payload` + one `clawpack` `.tgz`; `files` and `clawpack` cannot be mixed.\n- Derive stored file metadata and npm-pack artifact metadata from uploaded bytes server-side, then pass only that server-built request to internal publish actions.\n- Move browser plugin publishing to the same multipart HTTP boundary and allow signed-in browser sessions on that publish route without widening the JSON/storageId publish path.\n- Document the package publish boundary in docs/specs.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `bun run --cwd packages/schema build`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts --testNamePattern \"package publish|multipart package publish|multipart ClawPack\" --reporter=dot`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts --testNamePattern \"browser session auth\" --reporter=dot`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/packages.public.test.ts --testNamePattern \"publish\" --reporter=dot`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/lib/clawpack.test.ts src/lib/packageUpload.test.ts src/lib/uploadFiles.test.ts src/__tests__/plugins-publish-route.test.tsx --reporter=dot`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/lib/publishLimits.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/clawhub test:src -- src/cli/commands/packages.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run lint`\n- `bun run format:check`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit --pretty false`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit --pretty false`\n- `bunx tsc --noEmit --pretty false`\n- `git diff --check origin/main`\n\n## Not Run\n\n- `bunx convex codegen` locally; this checkout has no `CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT` configured.\n",
